The Verilog/SystemVerilog parser seems to get confused with certain signals (possibly because of signal types??).

The following code is highlighted correctly (all signals are the same color):

```SystemVerilog
interface ahb_if(input bit HCLK);

   logic [20:0] HADDR;
   logic        HWRITE;
   logic [1:0]  HTRANS;
   logic [7:0]  HWDATA;
   logic [7:0]  HRDATA;

   modport Master (input HCLK, output HADDR, output HWRITE, output HTRANS,
                   output HWDATA, input HRDATA);

   modport Slave (input HCLK, input HADDR, input HWRITE, input HTRANS,
                  input HWDATA, output HRDATA);

endinterface : ahb_if
```

However, this code is highlighted incorrectly. The first two signals (`A` and `DQ`) are highlighted as signals, but the following three signals (`CE_b`, `WE_b`, and `OE_b`) are not highlighted at all.

```SystemVerilog
interface sram_if(input bit CLK);

   logic [20:0] A;
   wire  [7:0]  DQ;
   logic        CE_b;
   logic        WE_b;
   logic        OE_b;

   modport Master (input CLK, output A, inout DQ, output CE_b,
                   output WE_b, output OE_b);

   modport Slave (input CLK, input A, input DQ, input CE_b,
                  input WE_b, input OE_b);


endinterface : sram_if
```

